Here is a practical **TODO list for ERP CapSpec definitions**.

```markdown
# ERP CapSpec Definition TODO List

## 1. Define the CapSpec foundation

- [ ] Finalize the official name: **CapSpec**
- [ ] Freeze the CapSpec core document structure
- [ ] Freeze required fields for every capability definition
- [ ] Freeze capability versioning rules
- [ ] Freeze naming rules (`domain.action`)
- [ ] Freeze lifecycle states (`Draft`, `Stable`, `Deprecated`, `Retired`)
- [ ] Freeze common error model
- [ ] Freeze common semantics fields (`idempotent`, `sideEffect`, `transactional`)
- [ ] Freeze contract test file format
- [ ] Freeze example file format

---

## 2. Define the capability type system

- [ ] Finalize top-level capability types
  - [ ] service
  - [ ] event-handler
  - [ ] data
  - [ ] resource
  - [ ] ui
  - [ ] integration
- [ ] Define signature model for each type
- [ ] Define validation method for each type
- [ ] Define test strategy for each type
- [ ] Define file layout conventions for each type

---

## 3. Define common shared schemas

